pageContext.claim: “Democrats in Congress have already signed up for a socialist takeover of health care that would eliminate the private insurance of 1.6 million people from Nevada.”
pageContext.analysis: This is wrong on several levels. Trump is referring to Sen. Bernie Sanders's bill to institute Medicare-for-All, which Nevada's Jacky Rosen does not support. That plan would reimburse private hospitals, not socialize the health care system or kill private insurers. In theory, more people would be covered, not fewer. Democrats in Congress have not all "signed up" for Sanders's plan.
